00074     BaseIntersectionIterator(C* airFrames, simtime_t from, simtime_t to) :
00075       intervals(airFrames), from(from), to(to) {
00076       endIt = intervals->lower_bound(from);
00077 
00078       if(endIt != intervals->end()) {
00079         startIt = endIt->second.begin();
00080       }
00081       alreadyNext = true;

00088     AirFrame* next() {
00089       if(endIt == intervals->end())
00090         return 0;
00091 
00092       //"alreadyNext" indicates that some previous iterator
00093       //function has already increased the intern iterators
00094       //to a yet unchecked values. This happen after
00095       //initialisation of the iterator and when an element
00096       //is erased.
00097       if(alreadyNext)
00098         alreadyNext = false;
00099       else
00100         startIt++;
00101 
00102       while(endIt != intervals->end()) {
00103         while(startIt != endIt->second.end()) {
00104           if(startIt->first <= to) {
00105             return startIt->second;
00106           }
00107           startIt++;
00108         }
00109         endIt++;
00110         if(endIt == intervals->end())
00111           return 0;
00112         startIt = endIt->second.begin();
00113       }
00114       return 0;
00115     }
00116   };

00138     void eraseAirFrame() {
00139       //check if our iterator points to a valid entry
00140       if(endIt == intervals->end())
00141         return;
00142 
00143       //erase AirFrame from list
00144       startIt = endIt->second.erase(startIt);
00145 
00146       //check if we've deleted the last entry in the list

00148         //check if we deleted the only entry in the list
